==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''skapja-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[skeppa]], Gothic [[𐌲𐌰𐍃𐌺𐌰𐍀𐌾𐌰𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'ʃieppan/

===Verb===
{{Unicode|'''scieppan'''}} (class VI strong: '''sciepþ''' ‘he creates’, {{Unicode|'''scōp'''}} ‘he created’, '''scōpon''' ‘they created’, ('''ġe''')'''scapen''' past participle)
# to [[create]], to [[form]]
# to [[mould]] or [[shape]] into a specific form

